  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The main objective of this study is to compare the rate of anal incontinence (measured by the
      Wexner score, qualitative and quantitative (&gt; 4)) at 3 months post partum among primiparas
      with vaginal tears ≥ 2nd degree who receive a sphincter injury screening at delivery by
      conducting a sphincter ultrasound in the delivery room versus a similar group of women who do
      not benefit from screening.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
